news.title: Odisha: 100-day challenge to complete PMAY houses
news.para: In a letter to municipal commissioners and executive officers of the ULBs, additional secretary of the urban development department, Debasis Singh, said under PMAY-U, 28,472 units are under various stages of construction, which must be completed before December 2024.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP inspects 22 lifts in Sobha City after residents file plaints
news.para: Not just this, the residents have approached almost all higher authorities, including CM window, DTCP, DHBVN and others, for replacement of the lifts for safety of residents and preventing any mishap but no concrete action has been taken so far.

news.title: Landowner, developer can't block layout access: Karnataka HC
news.para: A division bench comprising Chief Justice Prasanna B Varale and Justice Krishna S Dixit made this observation while dismissing the writ appeal filed by Pabba Reddy Kodandarami Reddy, a landowner from Bellandur in Bengaluru.

news.title: Ghaziabad mayor warns of fines on townships with no waste processing plants
news.para: “We will be conducting surprise inspections in these societies to check where the builders and AOA are dumping the garbage. If they are found without a processing plant for segregation of wet and dry garbage, we will issue notice and impose a fine of up to Rs 1 lakh,” said mayor Dayal.

news.title: After tremors, Navi Mumbai builders take stock of earthquake resistance
news.para: ​A day later, builders and civic officials said housing and commercial towers, as well as other structures in Navi Mumbai are safe as the base and plinth of buildings are made earthquake-resistant at the time of construction.

news.title: Kolkata: Large realty projects to pay water infrastructure development fee
news.para: The proposal, already passed by KMC House, will be effective December 1. The levy will be imposed on all upcoming realty projects that exceed 2,000sq m (20,000sq ft) in size with the civic body charging Rs 100/ sq m (1,000 sq ft).

news.title: Additional housing loans for stalled real estate projects to be treated as standard credit
news.para: A communication in this regard was sent out to banks last month, people familiar with the matter told ET. The government had in 2019 set up a Special Window for Affordable and Mid-Income Housing (SWAMIH) Investment Fund to help complete stalled housing projects.

news.title: Court allows ED's plea for CCTV at former HDIL promoter's home
news.para: In a plea submitted by special public prosecutor Kavita Patil, the ED said he may tamper with evidence and influence witnesses and dispose of unidentified assets.

news.title: Noida: More built-up area for Amrapali projects, sale to fund completion
news.para: The GNIDA is expecting a revenue windfall of Rs 450 crore by allowing extra floor area ratio (FAR) in the projects. NBCC is working under the supervision of Supreme Court-appointed receiver R Venkataramani and is completing five residential projects of Amrapali – Centurion, Smart City, Leisure Park, Leisure Valley and Dream Valley in Greater Noida.

news.title: LG urges Delhi RERA to revisit order, says it stalled property registration in the city
news.para: Saxena on Tuesday met the chairman and members of Delhi RERA along with the Chief Secretary and divisional commissioner at Raj Niwas to address the issue.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh RERA ensures possession of plots after six years with delay interest
news.para: Sanjay Bhoosreddy, chairman, UP-RERA said, "During virtual hearing we come across such matters in which both parties want to settle matter mutually. Hence, we transfer such matters to the Conciliation forum where the Conciliator mediates in the matter for settlement."

news.title: Evergrande Property Services' unit starts legal proceedings against China Evergrande
news.para: The unit, Jinbi Property Management Company, has commenced the proceedings for the recovery of about 2 billion yuan ($279.60 million) deposit certificate pledge guarantees.

news.title: Swedish property groups should cut debt, financial watchdog says
news.para: Sweden's property sector, which increased borrowing when rates were low, is struggling with high interest costs and falling property values as the economy slows.

news.title: Madras HC stays ED's summons to Tamil Nadu officials in illegal sand mining probe
news.para: ​A division bench comprising Justices S S Sundar and Sundar Mohan granted the interim stay on the petition filed by state public department secretary K Nanthakumar.

news.title: The Executive Centre plans to invest over Rs 240 crore to expand in Middle East
news.para: The Executive Centre is looking to add at least one lakh sq ft in Middle East in the coming years. The total investment that it is looking to make in Dubai is AED 62,750,000 (approximately Rs 142.48 crore) while in Abu Dhabi it's investment is about Rs 98 crore.

news.title: D B Realty sells 2.91% stake in company to raise Rs 301 crore
news.para: The funds so infused has enabled D B Realty to retire its entire debt and therefore the company on a standalone basis shall be debt free on a standalone basis on or before November 30, 2023, the company said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Ahmedabad's wetlands disappearing at alarming rate
news.para: The city’s lakes have been degrading and disappearing at an alarming rate, according to a new study by researchers at Gujarat University’s department of botany, bioinformatics and climate change impacts management.

news.title: Silkyara: Construction waste dumps a call to disaster
news.para: For half a decade now, villagers of Manjh Gaon and Vaana Gaon have been living under the looming threat of toxicwaste.

news.title: Chandigarh: Protest against eviction notices to 63 houses
news.para: ​The residents of the colony joined the protest. Unit president H S Lucky emphasised the historic role of the Congress Party in upliftment of the weaker sections of the society through comprehensive housing schemes.

news.title: Gurugram: No nod yet, work on Dwarka expressway service roads may begin only in Jan
news.para: Officials said the approval and allotment process is likely to be completed soon and the construction work will begin by January.
